cast.text:
the thing i probably miss the most from using roamresearch.com daily was the ability to copy references to individual blocks

roams' atomic unit of thought/data is a 'block' -- a bullet point that can be at the parent level or any Nth level of indentation

not only was the inherent structure helpful for organizing thoughts, but it also let me reference chunks of my convo(eg. I could link to a specific argument or link from earlier in my notes)

doing that sort of block-level referencing(as opposed to page-level referencing) has been very hard to find in other tools, and while i don't really have a replacement for that particular feature i wish i did
